summary: My favorite Loki moment in Ragnarok is when he pads Thor's shoulder after the two earth girls mention his break up with Jane....
body: My favorite Loki moment in Ragnarok is when he pads Thor’s shoulder after the two earth girls mention his break up with Jane. It’s such a small moment and yet it shows that Loki cares for Thor, that he’s his brother after all. He might not be able to change anything about it and probably doesn’t want to say something, because Thor is still pretty mad at him in that moment and yet he wants to make sure that Thor knows he’s there for him.

title: Fears and Facing Them
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2G3Oe4u

by Stuckylover4ever

Fears are something that everyone has. The Avengers is no different than the rest of the world. They are all afraid of something. On a daily bases, you could see an Avenger trying to overcome their fear. It was a lengthy and challenging process, but they all want to say that their fear couldn’t and wouldn’t get them. Some of their fears were normal, but others were not. Certain Avengers had fears that were easy to spot while others had other fears that were harder to detect. Follow the Avengers as they face their fears. Can they overcome them or will the fear swallow them whole? Join them on their way to facing the most significant threat they ever faced: their fear. Can they do it? Or will the fear take them over?
